Thanks Oliver, Humm, tricky, ok the two things that spring to mind: 1. Use category classes if all the courses are in the same category id. 2. Use SCSS instead (in the theme 'scss' setting), that has a syntax that will help with the repetition.  Thus you can have a long list of course classes with then the modifications within, something like: 
```text
.course-X, .course-Y, .course-Z {
    .gradingform_rubric .criteria {display:table}
    #rubric-advancedgrading{width:100%}
}
```
 sort of thing.  This is off the top of my head and totally untested!  I realise that this is similar to what you're saying, but I don't think there is any other way without code changes, as t o get 'MYCUSTOMCLASS' etc, into the body classes for a given course will need code changes. G
